infos.info: ORCHESTRA: Pianist: Rosa Rio - VOCALIST(S): The Paul Taubman Trio - 15, 30, and 60 minute programs aired on CBC and NBC. - Also titled: 'Matinee with Bob and Ray'??ÃÂ and 'Pick and Play with Bob and Ray,'??ÃÂ This title (NBC,1953) featured a quiz segment wherein a contestant, selected from the studio audience, first chose a number and then attempted to answer a question associated with it. Players received prizes whether they answered correctly or not, but strove to acquire the most correct answers to win a jackpot of merchandise gifts. - Originally aired locally over WHDH in Boston.

The show animated the air Monday through Saturday on WHDH. The weekday half-hours were broadcast live; the Saturday shows were usually 25 minutes. The lightening-wit duo dazzled fans with their spontaneous humor. An off-the-wall quip may inspire the appearance of a familiar character, such as home economics guru Mary Margaret McGoon espousing wobbly guidance. A truckload of unrehearsed personalities, inevitably named 'Sturdley,' were a beloved runner of the show. This show featured one of the many soap opera satires, Just Fancy Dan. A treasure of Bob and Ray shows are available online, including the REPS site. You can check out 238 Bob and Ray clips and 434 Bob and Ray clips at the Internet Archive
